FortyTwo BBS on Ubuntu 25.10
============================

Tested development platform
---------------------------

The currently tested host platform for FortyTwo BBS development is:

- Ubuntu 25.10
- x86_64
- glibc-based Linux
- rootless Podman

No other Linux distribution, Linux version, processor architecture or BSD
system is currently documented as supported or compatible.

Debian is planned as the first container deployment target, but is not yet a
supported platform.


Development status
------------------

FortyTwo BBS is pre-alpha software intended exclusively for development,
code review and isolated testing.

There is currently no supported production installation, public deployment
or upgrade procedure.

Do not run the inherited `SETUP.sh` script. It still implements the historical
MBSE BBS installation model, creates legacy system accounts and modifies
system configuration files.

Personal operating-system accounts for BBS users are not part of the intended
FortyTwo BBS architecture.


Build requirements
------------------

A developer build on Ubuntu 25.10 requires at least:

- GCC and the standard C development toolchain
- GNU Make
- a POSIX-compatible shell
- glibc development headers
- Git and the required Autoconf build files

Optional features may use:

- zlib development files
- bzip2 development files
- iconv support
- GeoIP development files
- external archive programs
- external editors
- external virus scanners

The exact package list and automated installation procedure are still being
reviewed and will be documented only after they have been reproduced on a
clean Ubuntu 25.10 test system.


Rootless Podman
---------------

A rootless Podman test image has been built and started successfully on the
development host.

The current test runtime uses fixed service accounts. BBS users are intended
to become internal application identities with stable server-generated IDs,
not personal Unix or container accounts.

The Podman configuration is still a development setup and must not be treated
as a supported public deployment.


Network access
--------------

Telnet and SSH access have been tested locally on Ubuntu 25.10 and inside the
rootless Podman test environment.

The current examples listen only on localhost and are available under:

`examples/fortytwo-access`

SSH is restricted and starts only FortyTwo BBS through a forced command.
Command execution, forwarding, tunnelling, SCP and SFTP are disabled.

Public new-user registration remains disabled until registration and
authentication have been migrated completely to the internal BBS identity
system.


